prompt:
Add a new public function called IsEven to Calculator.calr that checks if a number is even. It takes i32 parameter n and returns bool. Use the modulo operator to check if n % 2 equals 0. Use function ID f003.

Use this exact pattern:
§F{f003:IsEven:pub}
  §I{i32:n}
  §O{bool}
  §S (or (and result (== (% n 2) 0)) (and (not result) (!= (% n 2) 0)))
  §R (== (% n 2) 0)
§/F{f003}

The postcondition ensures the result correctly reflects whether n is even.
